block content
  #main
    //canvas#lolcanvas(width='150', height='150', style='position:absolute;z-index:-100;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%')
    img#bg(src="images/homepage.png")
    img#map_overlay(src="images/map_overlay.png")
    a.mlh-trust-badge(href='https://mlh.io/?utm_campaign=Trust%20Badge', target='_blank')
      img(src='https://s3.amazonaws.com/logged-assets/trust-badge/s2016.png', alt='MLH Official - Spring 2016')
    section#canvas
      .jumbotron
        .container.text-center
          img#logo(src='images/logo.svg')
        .container.text-center
          a(href='http://my.mlh.io/oauth/authorize?client_id=25cec58cf6428c907062132f2fc53b817348d2512dd02b0874a60689e1b7f0c7&redirect_uri=http%3A%2F%2Foxhack.herokuapp.com%2Fsuccess&response_type=token') Apply Now
    section#about
      .container
        .row
          .col-md-4.pull-left
            h1.text-center
              span About
            p OxfordHack has first been organised in 2015 and we are returning to host an even bigger and better hackathon this year. The theme this year is "Harry Potter" and it's our little gimmick to add a bit more fun to what should already be an awesome weekend.
    section#map-container.container-fluid
    section#faq
      .container
        .row
          .col-md-12
            h1
              span FAQ
        .row
          .col-md-4
            h3 What is a Hackathon?
            p Hackathons are where thoughts become things, collaborating, coding and creating literally anything. Attendees work in teams of up to four people to create a hack, web, app, hardware or anything.
          .col-md-4
            h3 When is OxfordHack?
            p Registration for OxfordHack will open at 6:00PM and start at 9:30PM Friday April 19st until the morning of the 21st.
          .col-md-4
            h3 What if I have another question?
            p Tweet us at 
              a(href='http://twitter.com/hackupc') SOCIAL
              |  or drop us a line at 
              a(href='mailto:info@hackupc.com') EMAIL
        .row
          .col-md-4
            h3 Do you have a code of conduct?
            a(href='http://static.mlh.io/docs/mlh-code-of-conduct.pdf') Yes
            | . tl;dr: Be excellent to each other.
          .col-md-4
            h3 What if I don't have a team?
            p No need to worry! Part of the fun of a hackathon is meeting new people. We will have time at the beginning of the event for everyone to meet and form teams.
          .col-md-4
            h3 What can I build?
            p Web, mobile, hardware, anything is on the table. Projects will be judged based on creativity, technical difficulty, polish and usefulness by a panel of industry judges.
        .row
          .col-md-4
            h3 Where is it being held?
            p Oxford
          .col-md-4
            h3 Who can attend?
            p Students from universities and high schools from all around the world.
          .col-md-4
            h3 How much does it cost?
            p OxfordHack is free for all accepted hackers. We provide you WiFi, meals, swag, and workspace. We also have a limited number of travel scholarships - up to 50€ if you're traveling from outside of Oxford.
        .row
          .col-md-4
            h3 What should I bring?
            p All attendees must bring a valid ID for admission. Other common checklist items include: laptops, sleeping bags, chargers and toiletries. If you want to shower, bring a towel!
          .col-md-4
            h3 How big can teams be?
            p Teams of up to four are welcome. You can also hack solo if you want!
    section#sponsors
      .container
        .row
          .col-md-12
            h1
              span Sponsors
            p OxfordHack gives companies the opportunity to get in touch with some of the most talented university students here at Oxford.
            p You can find our sponsorship packages 
              a(href='#') here
              | . If you are interested or have any questions feel free to contact us at 
              a(href='#') sponsor@oxfordhack.com
    section#resources
      .container
        .row
          .col-md-12
            h1
              span Resources
            p If you are a beginner, here are links to some awesome online tutorials that cater to almost every imaginable programming language out there.
        .row
          .col-md-2.logo
            span.helper
            a(href="https://www.codecademy.com/", target='_blank')
              img(src='images/codecademy.png')
          .col-md-2.logo
            span.helper
            a(href="https://www.edx.org/", target='_blank')
              img(src='https://www.edx.org/sites/default/files/theme/edx-logo-header.png')
          .col-md-2.logo
            span.helper
            a(href="https://www.codewars.com/", target='_blank')
              img(src='http://d3l8wp33uu8nxs.cloudfront.net/assets/landing/logo-964e5b1c06db93a4914f490c8fd5cc03.png')
          .col-md-2.logo
            span.helper
            a(href="https://www.udacity.com/", target='_blank')
              img(src='https://endor-dev.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/sites/566671d2495b2d0018000000/theme/images/rebrand/logo-wordmark.svg?1456958557')
          .col-md-2.logo
            span.helper
            a(href="https://www.freecodecamp.com/", target='_blank')
              img(src='https://s3.amazonaws.com/freecodecamp/freecodecamp_logo.svg')
          .col-md-2.logo
            span.helper
            a(href='https://www.udemy.com/', target='_blank')
              img(src='https://www.udemy.com/staticx/udemy/images/v5/logo-green.svg')
